        The Preimplantation Diagnosis (DPI) may be offered to couples at risk of transmitting a
        serious genetic disease to their offspring
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age&gt; or = 18 years

          -  Couples at risk of transmitting cystic fibrosis

          -  asking for a PGD in Strasbourg

          -  DNA samples available at the laboratory for:

               -  The couple

               -  A related with CFTR status known

               -  Having signed an informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Inability to give informed consent (understanding difficulties...)
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
